## Conversation
User asked to scan the entire google-adk TS stack for type precision and fix:
(1) any/undefined/null that isn't actually true, (2) lazy `?` where upstream
is required, (3) over-defensive code that hurts readability. Verified every
duck type against the REAL @google/adk@1.2.0 + @google/genai .d.ts installed in
node_modules (ground truth), not from memory.

## Actions (slice 01 — owns the core duck types + run lifecycle + helpers)
googleAdk.types.ts:
- AdkPart.text: unknown -> string (genai Part.text is string | undefined; kept `?`)
- Removed dead fields never read by the impl: AdkPart.thought, AdkBlob.data,
  AdkEvent.id, AdkInvocationContext.branch, AdkCallbackContext.userContent.
- AdkEvent.content: dropped `| null` (genai/adk Content is never null, only undefined).
- AdkInvocationContext.agent/session -> required; AdkSession.id/appName/userId
  -> required (all required upstream; real types stay assignable to the duck
  types, verified by tsc against the test which drives the plugin with REAL
  @google/adk objects).
googleAdk.ts:
- toJsonSafe(): any -> unknown (all callers stringify / accept unknown).
- partToWire: String(part.text) -> part.text (text is now string).
- finishReasonString / contentToOutputMessage param: unknown ->
  `string | null | undefined`, dropped the now-redundant String() (FinishReason
  is a genai string enum).
- beforeRun/onEvent/afterRun: removed gratuitous `?.`/ternary guards on
  params.invocationContext (ADK-guaranteed) and ic.agent/ic.session (now
  required). Kept the empty-string `!invocationId` guard.

## Errors & Mistakes
