===================================================================
User review comment on partToWire's return: asked for a more precise/idiomatic
type than the loose object. Replaced `type WirePart = Record<string, unknown>`
with a discriminated union on `type`:
  | {type:'text'; content:string}
  | {type:'blob'; mime_type:string}
  | {type:'tool_call'; id:string; name:string; arguments:unknown}
  | {type:'tool_call_response'; id:string; response:unknown}
partToWire/contentToParts/systemInstructionParts all typecheck against it; the
compiler now catches a misspelled/missing wire-part field. Verified tsc esm+cjs,
prettier, slice-01 jest 5/5.

Note: toJsonSafe was deliberately LEFT as-is (robust bigint+cycle+catch
safe-stringify). User asked whether ADK users hit bigint/cycles; answer: not the
common path, but reachable via tool RETURN values (cycles realistic, bigint
rare). The branches aren't crash-protection (the try/catch is) — they preserve a
degraded value instead of nulling the whole result. User did not ask to simplify.
